0Prime%20Minister%20Kristen%20Michal%20told%20Politico%20that%20it%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Bmessage%20that%20Estonia%20has%20been%20advocating%20for%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20clear%20signal%20to%20Putin%20that%20he%20should%20not%20dare%20to%20test%20NATO's%20nerves%20and%20that%20we%20are%20prepared%20for%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%20Northern%20Group%20partners'%20meeting%20last%20year%2C%20Estonia's%20defense%20minister%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FMoD_Estonia%2Fstatus%2F1793627157601915329%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eurged%3C%2Fa%3E%20allies%20to%20increase%20spending%20to%202.5%25%20to%20counter%20the%20threat%20of%20Russian%20aggression.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESweden%2C%20which%20has%20also%20increased%20defense%20spending%20since%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%202022%2C%20also%20backed%20the%20call%20for%20increased%20spending.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20a%20broad%20consensus%20in%20Sweden%20that%20we%20need%20to%20invest%20more%20in%20our%20defense%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20country's%20foreign%20minister%2C%20Maria%20Malmer%20Stenergard%2C%20said%2C%20per%20Politico.%20%26quot%3BUS%20governments%20have%20long%20urged%20European%20countries%20to%20increase%20their%20defense%20spending%20and%20to%20bear%20more%20of%20their%20own%20defense%20costs.%20We%20share%20this%20view.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELithuania%20has%20also%20prioritized%20defense%20spending%20amid%20the%20growing%20Russian%20threat.%20Its%20president%2C%20Gitanas%20Naus%C4%97da%2C%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FGitanasNauseda%2Fstatus%2F1866494678100533619%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecalled%20on%3C%2Fa%3E%20European%20countries%20to%20%26quot%3Bshow%20more%20support%20for%20the%20US%20global%20agenda%26quot%3B%20by%20increasing%20their%20share%20of%20the%20defense%20burden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20his%20part%2C%20NATO%20Secretary%20General%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%