662c9f1f93b6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221061%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20reader%20is%20not%20pictured.%3Cp%3EMorsa%20Images%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ffor-love-and-money%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFor%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20column%20from%20Business%20Insider%20answering%20your%20relationship%20and%20money%20questions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20week%2C%20a%20reader%20is%20tired%20of%20fighting%20with%20their%20husband%20over%20who%20inherits%20their%20estate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOur%20columnist%20says%20the%20fight%20isn't%20just%20about%20who%20gets%20the%20money%20later%2C%20but%20who%20it%20belongs%20to%20now.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGot%20a%20question%20for%20our%20columnist%3F%20Write%20to%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%20using%20%3Ca%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fforms%2Fd%2Fe%2F1FAIpQLSdhFnAxR57cNtGiwNUd-6vLAYAc75grvly3C10-854vFP4arw%2Fviewform%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethis%20Google%20form%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EDear%20For%20Love%20%26amp%3B%20Money%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20have%20been%20married%20for%20eight%20years.%20This%20is%20my%20husband's%20first%20legal%20marriage%20and%20my%20third.%20I%20have%20one%20child%2C%20and%20he%20has%20one%20sister.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EAll%20our%20assets%20combined%20hold%20a%20value%20of%20about%20%241.25%20million.%20We%20have%20zero%20debt%20and%20have%20paid%20off%20our%20house.%20We%20tried%20doing%20a%20will%20online%2C%20and%20it%20was%20a%20mess.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20constantly%20fight%20about%20dividing%20the%20estate%20between%20his%20sister%20(who%20is%20wealthier%20than%20us%20and%20does%20not%20need%20the%20money)%20and%20my%20daughter%2C%20who%20is%20married%20and%20has%20two%20children.%20I%20suggested%20leaving%20his%20sister%20%2450%2C000%20as%20a%20gesture.%20We%20got%20nowhere.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20we%20both%20die%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20does%20his%20sister%20have%20a%20claim%20to%2050%25%20of%20the%20estate%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ESincerely%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EPlaying%20the%20Odds%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDear%20Playing%20the%20Odds%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20you%20both%20die%20at%20the%20same%20time%20without%20a%20will%2C%20your%20estate%20will%20be%20frozen%20and%20combed%20through%2C%20and%20no%20one%20will%20get%20the%20money%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time.%20When%20the%20money%20is%20finally%20released%2C%20his%20sister%20will%20have%20a%20claim%20to%20it%2C%20although%20your%20daughter%20will%20likely%20take%20precedence.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20there%20are%20no%20guarantees%20on%20how%20these%20things%20will%20work%20out.%20You%20asked%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20you%20die%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20but%20what%20if%20you%20don't%3F%20What%20if%20you%20go%20first%3F%20Your%20husband%20would%20get%20the%20money%20and%20be%20under%20no%20obligation%20to%20leave%20anything%20to%20your%20daughter%20and%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYour%20best%20option%20is%20to%20find%20a%20compromise%20and%20write%20a%20will.%20You%20mentioned%20trying%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-to-make-a-will-without-a-lawyer%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ewrite%20a%20will%20yourself%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20an%20online%20template%2C%20which%20I%20understand%20can%20feel%20less%20daunting%20and%20expensive%20than%20hiring%20an%20estate%20planner.%20Still%2C%20you%20have%20considerable%20assets%20to%20leave.%20Hire%20an%20estate%20planning%20attorney.%20The%20peace%20of%20mind%20that%20will%20come%20with%20putting%20this%20arduous%20and%20complex%20task%20into%20their%20capable%20hands%20will%20be%20worth%20every%20penny.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20you%20make%20an%20appointment%20with%20a%20professional%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20ensure%20you%20aren't%20just%20hiring%20someone%20to%20witness%20you%20and%20your%20husband%20go%2012%20rounds%20over%20his%20sister%20and%20your%20daughter's%20shares.%20So%20first%2C%20you%20must%20reach%20a%20compromise.%20You%20said%20he%20wasn't%20impressed%20with%20your%20suggestion%20to%20leave%20his%20sister%20%2450%2C000%2C%20but%20you%20didn't%20mention%20how%20much%20he%20wants%20to%20leave%20her.%20I%20will%20assume%20he%20wants%20to%20divide%20it%20between%20the%20two%20women%20equally%2C%20which%20you%20don't%20agree%20with%20due%20to%20need.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYour%20husband's%20resistance%20to%20leaving%20the%20bulk%20of%20your%20shared%20estate%20to%20your%20daughter%2C%20despite%20his%20sister's%20lack%20of%20need%2C%20makes%20me%20think%20the%20issue%20isn't%20about%20who%20will%20get%20the%20money%20later%20but%20who%20it%20belongs%20to%20now%20%E2%80%94%20you%20or%20him.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20are%20taught%20from%20infancy%20to%20share%20and%20that%20sharing%20is%20as%20simple%20as%20drawing%20a%20line%20down%20the%20middle%20or%20taking%20an%20equal%20amount%20of%20turns.%20The%20truth%20about%20sharing%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%2050%2F50%20division%20undermines%20the%20sense%20of%20total%20autonomy%20that%20comes%20with%20ownership.%20The%20feeling%20of%20independence%20is%20a%20zero-sum%20game.%20You%20either%20answer%20to%20someone%20or%20you%20don't.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDue%20to%20this%2C%20the%20compromise%20partnership%20demands%20of%20us%20rarely%20feels%20like%20a%20win%2Fwin.%20Instead%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20what%20it%20is%3A%20giving%20up%20part%20of%20what%20we%20want%2C%20an%20emotional%20admission%20that%20the%20decision%20we're%20arguing%20over%20was%20never%20ours%20alone%20to%20make.%20So%2C%20all%20too%20often%2C%20we%20try%20to%20outrun%20this%20admission%20by%20fighting%20to%20get%20our%20way%20over%20our%20partner's.%20We'll%20even%20throw%20our%20opponents%20a%20bone%20(or%20%2450%2C000)%20here%20and%20there%20to%20entice%20them%20to%20let%20us%20win.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20way%20these%20conflicts%20can%20resolve%20outside%20of%20everlasting%20gridlock%20or%20separation%20is%20to%20recognize%20that%20the%20triumph%20you%20feel%20after%20compromising%20isn't%20achieved%20by%20mostly%20getting%20your%20way%3B%20it's%20from%20recognizing%20that%20you%20and%20your%20partner%20overcame%20your%20self-interests%20and%20achieved%20a%20solution%20that%20was%20best%20for%20your%20marriage%2C%20not%20for%20yourselves.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20means%20you%20must%20accept%20that%20your%20daughter's%20needs%20and%20his%20sister's%20lack%20of%20need%20have%20little%20to%20do%20with%20reaching%20a%20fair%20compromise%20with%20your%20husband.%20A%20fair%20compromise%20must%20reflect%20your%20estate's%20dual%20ownership%3A%20drawing%20a%20line%20down%20the%20middle%20with%20each%20of%20your%20beneficiaries%20getting%20half.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIf%20you%20are%20willing%20to%20make%20such%20a%20huge%20concession%2C%20your%20husband%20may%20feel%20inspired%20to%20do%20the%20same.%20Having%20been%20reassured%20that%20you%20understand%20half%20the%20estate%20belongs%20to%20him%2C%20he%20might%20have%20more%20clarity%20around%20questions%20of%20need.%20Perhaps%20he'll%20be%20more%20open%20to%20ideas%20like%20splitting%20the%20money%20between%20your%20daughter%20and%20his%20sister%2C%20but%20leaving%20the%20house%20to%20your%20daughter.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20signed%20your%20letter%20%26quot%3BPlaying%20the%20Odds%26quot%3B%2C%20and%20I%20wonder%20if%20you%20were%20referring%20to%20rolling%20the%20dice%20on%20your%20daughter's%20future%20by%20counting%20on%20outliving%20your%20spouse.%20Even%20if%20you%20take%20my%20advice%20and%20set%20up%20a%20will%20that%20divides%20your%20estate%20evenly%20between%20your%20sister-in-law%20and%20daughter%2C%20your%20daughter's%20future%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20a%20gamble.%20You%20can%20set%20up%20financial%20supports%20for%20your%20daughter%20and%20grandchildren%20while%20you're%20still%20alive.%20Open%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fhow-does-a-trust-fund-work-basics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etrust%20funds%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20their%20names%2C%20set%20up%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fstudent-loans%2F529-college-savings-plans-by-state%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E529%20plans%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20your%20grandchildren's%20college%20tuitions%2C%20and%20look%20for%20other%20ways%20to%20put%20them%20on%20the%20road%20toward%20future%20success%20now%2C%20with%20or%20without%20a%20million-dollar%20inheritance%20waiting%20in%20the%20wings.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20always%20say%20that%20the%20most%20challenging%20part%20of%20marriage%20is%20sharing%20a%20life.%20It%20may%20sound%20simple%2C%20but%20doing%20it%20is%20anything%20but.%20It%20means%20giving%20up%20half%20of%20your%20agenda%20in%20favor%20of%20another's%2C%20and%20this%20requires%20faith.%20Faith%20that%20when%20you%20give%20your%20spouse%20half%20of%20everything%2C%20they%20will%20do%20the%20same%20%E2%80%94%20an%20even%20trade.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERooting%20for%20you%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E