%2C%20dating%20back%20to%202019%20when%20he%20first%20suggested%20the%20US%20should%20purchase%20the%20territory.%20Greenland's%20strategic%20location%20has%20been%20valuable%20to%20the%20US%20since%20the%20Cold%20War%20era%2C%20with%20President%20Harry%20Truman%20previously%20offering%20to%20buy%20the%20Danish%20territory%20for%20%24100%20million%20in%20gold%20in%201946%20-%20a%20proposal%20the%20Danes%20declined.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20idea%20of%20one%20sovereign%20nation%20buying%20territory%20from%20another%20may%20seem%20unusual%2C%20there%20are%20precedents.%20The%20US%20has%20purchased%20several%20territories%20in%20the%20past%2C%20including%20the%20Louisiana%20Purchase%2C%20Alaska%2C%20and%20the%20US%20Virgin%20Islands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDavid%20Barker%20pointed%20out%20that%20Greenland's%20value%20would%20increase%20if%20its%20role%20in%20US%20defence%20is%20considered%2C%20as%20it%20would%20correlate%20with%20the%20size%20of%20the%20US%20economy.%20But%20if%20the%20value%20is%20based%20only%20on%20minerals%2C%20the%20economy%20size%20wouldn't%20matter%20as%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22nofollow%2Cnoindex%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Ff6f9ac64-c3cd-42be-ab2e-c0a833787a30%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFinancial%20Times%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggested%20Greenland's%20resources%20could%20be%20worth%20%241.1%20trillion.%20But%20Mr%20Barker%20called%20this%20estimate%20unrealistic%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20US%20would%20not%20benefit%20fully%20from%20resource%20extraction%2C%20as%20companies%20would%20buy%20drilling%20and%20mining%20rights%2C%20factoring%20in%20their%20own%20costs%20and%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAcquiring%20Greenland%20might%20not%20be%20as%20simple%20as%20making%20a%20purchase.%20Trump's%20national%20defence%20concerns%20are%20driving%20his%20interest%20in%20Greenland%2C%20but%20the%20island's%20residents%20might%20not%20be%20eager%20to%20become%20part%20of%20the%20US.%20Greenland's%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Mute%20Bourup%20Egede%2C%20has%20said%20that%20the%20island%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20for%20sale%20and%20will%20never%20be%20for%20sale%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutting%20a%20price%20tag%20on%20a%20country%2C%20like%20Greenland%2C%20is%20complex.%20GDP%2C%20which%20measures%20a%20country's%20economic%20output%2C%20is%20often%20used%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20capture%20long-term%20potential%20or%20unmeasured%20resources.%20Greenland's%20GDP%20is%20around%20%243.236%20billion%2C%20but%20its%20true%20value%20includes%20future%20growth%20and%20untapped%20resources%20like%20minerals%20and%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20factors%2C%20such%20as%20quality%20of%20life%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20strategic%20location%2C%20also%20add%20value.%20Greenland%20has%20valuable%20unexploited%20resources%20not%20reflected%20in%20its%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20long%20maintained%20a%20military%20presence%20in%20Greenland%2C%20which%20is%20a%20NATO%20ally%2C%20said%20Nikola%20Swann%2C%20global%20head%20of%20governments%20and%20multilaterals%20at%20SwissThink.%20Access%20to%20Greenland's%20minerals%20like%20copper%20and%20lithium%2C%20critical%20for%20technology%20such%20as%20batteries%20and%20electric%20vehicles%2C%20might%20be%20a%20key%20factor%20for%20the%20US%2C%20Ms%20Swann%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20also%20mentioned%20the%20possibility%20of%20using%20military%20force%20or%20tariffs%20in%20negotiations%2C%20and%20Denmark's%20growing%20economy%2C%20driven%20by%20pharmaceutical%20exports%20to%20the%20US%2C%20adds%20further%20leverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20buying%20national%20assets%20like%20the%20Panama%20Canal%20is%20easier%2C%20buying%20land%20or%20territory%20today%20is%20rare.%20National%20pride%2C%20democracy%2C%20and%20international%20norms%20make%20such%20transactions%20unlikely.%20Greenland%20may%20have%20a%20price%2C%20but%20a%20deal%20would%20be%20hard%20to%20achieve%20in%20today's%20world.%20Everyone%20agrees%20that%20purchasing%20Greenland%20%26quot%3Bwould%20be%20the%20deal%20of%20the%20century%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Mr%20Barker.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1736679540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-01%2Fpao0iqfs_donald-trump-greenland-map-arctic-region-map_625x300_10_January_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-wants-to-buy-greenland-how-much-would-it-actually-cost-7456706%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20President-elect%20Donald%20Trump's%20desire%20to%20acquire%20Greenland%2C%20an%20autonomous%20territory%20of%20Denmark%2C%20comes%20with%20a%20hefty%20price%20tag%20-%20between%20%2412.5%20billion%20and%20%2477%20billion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-wants-to-buy-greenland-how-much-would-it-actually-cost-7456706%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20New%20Book%2C%20Amitabh%20Kant%20Recalls%20What%20PM%20Told%20Him%20An%20Hour%20Before%20G20%20Meet%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDelhi%20had%20decked%20up%20for%20the%20G20%20summit%2C%20world%20leaders%20had%20flown%20in%20and%20the%20Centre's%20bureaucratic%20machinery%20was%20working%20overtime%20to%20ensure%20a%20perfect%20show.%20But%20the%20summit's%20success%20depended%20on%20one%20question%3A%20will%20there%20be%20consensus%20in%20the%20Leaders'%20Declaration%3F%20And%20it%20is%20this%20question%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20asked%20Sherpa%20Amitabh%20Kant%20an%20hour%20before%20the%20summit%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kant%20has%20narrated%20this%20key%20exchange%20with%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20on%20the%20morning%20of%20September%209%2C%202023%20in%20his%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BHow%20India%20Scaled%20Mt%20G20%3A%20The%20Inside%20Story%20of%20the%20G20%20Presidency%26quot%3B%20(Rupa%20Publications).%20The%20Prime%20Minister%20had%20reached%20Bharat%20Mandapam%20to%20review%20the%20preparations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20to%20brief%20him%20on%20our%20progress%20so%20far.%20When%20he%20enquired%20about%20the%20Leaders'%20Declaration%2C%20I%20outlined%20the%20conflict%20between%20the%20US%20and%20China%20and%20informed%20him%20that%20the%20NDLD%20(New%20Delhi%20Leaders'%20Declaration)%20was%20still%20not%20finalised%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kant%20writes%20in%20his%20book%2C%20news%20agency%20PTI%20has%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20paused%20for%20a%20moment%2C%20wondering%20as%20to%20why%20bilateral%20issues%20were%20being%20raised%20in%20a%20multilateral%20meeting%2C%20before%20replying%20that%20he%20did%20not%20want%20to%20get%20into%20the%20procedures%20or%20the%20process%2C%20but%20wanted%20to%20see%20the%20result%20-%20a%20consensus%20-%20very%20soon.%20He%20expected%20the%20Sherpa%20to%20navigate%20and%20secure%20the%20final%20agreement%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20book%20details%20the%20gruelling%20work%20that%20made%20summit%20a%20success.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrime%20Minister%20had%20announced%20a%20consensus%20on%20the%2037-page%20declaration%20and%20its%20subsequent%20adoption%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20second%20session%20on%20the%20opening%20day%20of%20the%20summit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kant%20has%20detailed%20in%20his%20book%20how%20New%20Delhi%20managed%20to%20navigate%20geopolitical%20currents%20and%20bilateral%20issues%20to%20reach%20this%20consensus.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20text%20continued%20to%20face%20constant%20revisions%20and%20objections%20after%20300%20hours%20of%20negotiations%20over%20250%20bilateral%20meetings.%20The%20weight%20and%20seriousness%20of%20the%20negotiations%20were%20felt%20by%20all%20participants%2C%20but%20the%20pursuit%20of%20a%20mutually%20agreeable%20outcome%20still%20seemed%20far%20from%20reach%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20writes%20in%20the%20book.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20he%20writes%2C%20was%20%26quot%3Bacutely%20aware%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20stakes%20involved%20and%20had%20asked%20for%20regular%20briefings.%20%26quot%3BHe%20had%20asked%20me%20to%20send%20him%20urgent%20situation%20reports%20every%20two%20hours%2C%20a%20task%20that%20demanded%20immense%20multitasking%20and%20quick%20analysis.%20This%20constant%20communication%20kept%20PM%20Modi%20informed%2C%20but%20also%20spurred%20us%20into%20action%2C%20helping%20us%20map%20out%20the%20negotiations%20and%20take%20stock%20of%20our%20progress%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kant%20writes%20that%20Russia%20had%20insisted%20that%20the%20word%20'sanction'%20be%20included%20in%20the%20declaration.%20Extensive%20discussions%20were%20held%20with%20Alexander%20Pankin%2C%20Russia's%20Deputy%20Minister%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%2C%20to%20persuade%20them%20to%20reconsider%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stakes%20were%20high%2C%20as%20refusal%20to%20compromise%20would%20have%20left%20Russia%20isolated%20with%20a%2019-1%20vote%20against%20it.%20We%20finally%20had%20to%20tell%20Russia%20that%20this%20was%20not%20feasible%20and%20would%20not%20be%20accepted%20by%20other%20countries.%20We%20made%20it%20abundantly%20clear%20to%20Russia%20that%20its%20insistence%20on%20this%20matter%20put%20significant%20pressure%20on%20India%20and%20made%20it%20impossible%20for%20us%20to%20move%20forward%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kant%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20G20%20Sherpa%20has%20said%20that%20throughout%20the%20negotiations%2C%20G7%20countries%20--%20Canada%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20Italy%2C%20Japan%2C%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US%20--%20pressured%20India%20to%20invite%20Ukraine%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%2C%20but%20India's%20stance%20was%20to%20restrict%20the%20guest%20list%20to%20G20%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20Dr%20Jaishankar's%20advice%2C%20I%20had%20to%20inform%20the%20Russian%20negotiator%20that%20if%20they%20didn't%20agree%2C%20the%20first%20speaker%20following%20PM%20Modi's%20speech%20would%20be%20Zelenskyy.%20This%20bold%20and%20assertive%20negotiation%20tactic%20ultimately%20worked%2C%20and%20Russia%20relented%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Kant%20writes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20another%20hurdle.%20Mr%20Kant%20writes%20that%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Chinese%20team%20pointed%20out%20a%20bilateral%20challenge%20with%20the%20US%2C%20stemming%20from%20a%20part%20of%20the%20declaration%20that%20stated%20that%20the%202026%20G20%20Summit%20would%20be%20hosted%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20Sherpa%2C%20Mr%20Kant%20writes%2C%20explained%20that%20the%20US%20would%20not%20grant%20them%20visas%2C%20not%20even%20for%20their%20governor%20in%20Hong%20Kong.%20They%20would%20not%20agree%20to%20the%20geopolitical%20paras%20until%20they%20received%20a%20written%20guarantee%20that%20they%20would%20be%20issued%20visas%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20leaders'%20meeting%20started%20at%209%20am%20and%20Mr%20Kant%20held%20parallel%20negotiations%20from%209.30%20am%20to%2011.30%20am%20in%20a%20room%20adjacent%20to%20the%20Leaders'%20Hall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%2C%20along%20with%20(US%20Sherpa%20Mike)%20Pyle%20and%20Li%20(Kexin%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Chinese%20team)%2C%20hammered%20out%20the%20details%20of%20the%20letter.%20We%20opted%20to%20use%20the%20term%20'ensure'%20instead%20of%20'guarantee'.%20By%20noon%2C%20we%20had%20successfully%20resolved%20this%20bilateral%20matter%2C%20even%20though%20technically%20it%20was%20beyond%20the%20scope%20of%20India's%20role%20as%20G20%20Chair.%20All%20the%20countries%2C%20he%20says%2C%20were%20finally%20on%20board.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Kant%20writes%20that%20sealing%20a%20consensus%20on%20the%20first%20day%20of%20the%20summit%20was%20%26quot%3Bno%20small%20feat%26quot%3B%20and%20cites%20the%20example%20of%20the%202022%20Bali%20submit%2C%20where%20negotiations%20on%20the%20declaration%20text%20dragged%20into%20the%20final%20hours.